JENKINS SETUP AND PIPELINE CREATION (STEP BY STEP)

1 Install Java and Jenkins on Ubuntu
  After installing, start Jenkins using terminal:
  sudo systemctl start jenkins
  sudo systemctl enable jenkins

2 Open Jenkins in Browser
  Go to: http://localhost:8080

3 Get Initial Admin Password
  In terminal type:
  sudo su -
  cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword
  Copy the password and paste it into the browser.

4 Setup Jenkins
  Click on "Install Suggested Plugins"
  Wait for all plugins to install.

5 Create Admin User
  Enter details like:
  Username: admin
  Password: admin
  Email: admin@example.com

6 Install Required Plugins (if needed)
  Go to Manage Jenkins → Plugins
  Install:
  Git Plugin
  Pipeline Plugin

7 Create a Pipeline Job
  Go to Dashboard
  Click "New Item"
  Enter a name (example: MyPipeline)
  Select "Pipeline"
  Click OK
